     <p>
      <strong>
       <span style="font-size: medium;">
        Upcoming Activities of the ADT
        <br/>
       </span>
      </strong>
     </p>
     <p>
      <span style="font-size: small;">
       In winter and spring quarters of the 2018-2019 academic year, we are planning to host invited speakers to talk in our Scholarship of Teaching series, offer informal workshops for faculty to consult about teaching issues (in conjunction with
       <a href="https://ctl.ucr.edu/" target="_blank">
        Academic Engagement
       </a>
       ), and send out the call for nominations for our annual
       <a href="https://academyteachers.ucr.edu/awards/">
        teaching awards
       </a>
       .
      </span>
     </p>
     <p>
      If you have any questions or comments please contact
      <a href="mailto:mmaduro@ucr.edu" target="_blank">
       mmaduro@ucr.edu
      </a>
      .
     </p>
     <p>
      <strong>
       <span style="font-size: medium;">
        About the Academy
       </span>
      </strong>
     </p>
     <p>
      The Academy of Distinguished Teachers was founded in 2005 to recognize the accomplishments of outstanding teachers among the UCR faculty and to provide a range of services to help other UCR faculty members to improve their work in the classroom. The guiding philosophy of the Academy is that the campus succeeds only to the extent that its seeks excellence in teaching, research, and service. Efforts to develop teaching excellence are particularly important in research universities, where so much professional recognition depends on research accomplishments.
     </p>
     <p>
      Members of the Academy serve as teaching mentors for new faculty and contribute to the culture of teaching by organizing and taking part in seminars, colloquia, and workshops. It also reviews teaching-related initiatives and grant proposals from members of the campus community. The Academy solicits yearly nominations for Innovative Teaching and Junior Excellence in Teaching Awards. The
      <a href="https://ue.ucr.edu/" target="_blank">
       Office of Undergraduate Education
      </a>
      provides administrative support for and oversight of the Academy. The Academy serves as an advisory group to the Provost on issues related to teaching excellence.
     </p>
     <p>
      Academy membership is determined via deliberations of the Academy, drawing from the list of faculty that have been recognized for their achievements in teaching. The Academy's view is that candidates have already been vetted by one or more competitions and we have the privilege of further recognizing these amazing colleagues.
     </p>
     <p>
      Current members of the Academy of Distinguished Teachers:
     </p>
     <p>
      <a href="https://profiles.ucr.edu/app/home/profile/mmaduro" target="_blank">
       Morris F. Maduro
      </a>
      (Chair of Academy), Molecular, Cell and Systems Biology
      <br/>
      <a href="https://profiles.ucr.edu/app/home/profile/beyerman" target="_blank">
       Ward P. Beyermann
      </a>
      , Physics and Astronomy
      <br/>
      <a href="https://profiles.ucr.edu/app/home/profile/jcbriggs" target="_blank">
       John C. Briggs
      </a>
      , English
      <br/>
      <a href="https://profiles.ucr.edu/app/home/profile/gabyc" target="_blank">
       Gabriela Canalizo
      </a>
      , Physics and Astronomy
      <br/>
      <a href="http://philosophy.ucr.edu/carl-cranor/" target="_blank">
       Carl F. Cranor
      </a>
      , Philosophy
      <br/>
      <a href="http://cbns.ucr.edu/faculty/curras-collazo.html" target="_blank">
       Margarita Curras-Collazo
      </a>
      , Molecular, Cell and Systems Biology
      <br/>
      <a href="http://chem.ucr.edu/faculty.html?id=94" target="_blank">
       Jack F. Eichler
      </a>
      , Chemistry
      <br/>
      <a href="https://medschool.ucr.edu/faculty_research/clinical_profiles/bio.html?page=lyons_paul.html" target="_blank">
       Paul Lyons
      </a>
      , School of Medicine
      <br/>
      <a href="http://www.psychology.ucr.edu/faculty/murray/index.html" target="_blank">
       Carolyn Murray
      </a>
      , Psychology
      <br/>
      <a href="https://arthistory.ucr.edu/faculty/conrad-rudolph/" target="_blank">
       Conrad Rudolph
      </a>
      , History of Art
      <br/>
      <a href="http://wesslerlab.ucr.edu/" target="_blank">
       Sue Wessler
      </a>
      , Botany and Plant Sciences
     </p>
     <p>
      <strong>
       <span style="font-size: medium;">
        Fall 2018 Workshops for New Faculty
       </span>
      </strong>
     </p>
     <p>
      <span style="font-size: small;">
       Our fall workshops have concluded. We hope to offer these again in 2019-2010. While aimed primarily at new faculty, anyone who has been teaching for many years, or plans to have a career involving teaching, will likely benefit. Sessions are held in the
       <a href="http://ue.ucr.edu/tlc.html" target="_blank">
        Center for Teaching and Learning (CTL)
       </a>
       in the first floor of the Rivera Library.
      </span>
     </p>
     <p>
      <span style="color: #000000;">
       (1)    Course Design and Assessment – 3:30pm-4:30pm, Wed 10/10/2018
      </span>
      <br/>
      <span style="color: #000000;">
       (2)    Technology in (and outside) the Classroom – 3:30pm-4:30pm, Wed 10/24/2018
      </span>
      <br/>
      <span style="color: #000000;">
       (3)    Engagement in Large and Small Classes – 3:30pm-4:30pm, Wed 11/7/2018
      </span>
      <br/>
      <span style="color: #000000;">
       (4)    Can Writing be Integrated into Disciplinary Courses at UCR?  Past Practices and Possibilities in CHASS, CNAS, BCOE, and the School of Business, 3:30pm-4:30pm, Wed 11/14/2018
      </span>
      <br/>
      <span style="color: #000000;">
       (5)    Academic Advancement and Teaching Evaluations – 3:30pm-4:30pm, Wed 11/28/2018
      </span>
      <br/>
      <span style="color: #000000;">
       (6)    Wrap-Up and Additional Topics – 3:30pm-4:30pm, Wed 12/5/2018
      </span>
     </p>
     <p>
      If you have any suggestions for future workshop topics please contact
      <a href="mailto:mmaduro@ucr.edu" target="_blank">
       mmaduro@ucr.edu
      </a>
      .
     </p>
     <p>
     </p>
